[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hello all, I've been working on trying to lift a function <code>f : (a : α) → (b : α) → P a → P b → β</code> to the quotient map<br>\n<code>f' : (a : Quotient s) → (b : Quotient s) → P' a → P' b → β</code> where <code>P</code> is a predicate that also respects the equivalence relation defined by the <code>Setoid</code>, <code>s</code> (and consequently lifts to <code>P'</code>), but I've had little success with using the theorems in the <code>Quotient</code> module. Many thanks for the advice <span aria-label=\"pray\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f64f\" role=\"img\" title=\"pray\">:pray:</span> </p>\n<p>(p.s. I'm trying to avoid using Quotient.out)</p>",
        "id": 518359144,
        "sender_full_name": "Kin Yau James Wong",
        "timestamp": 1747329163
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe you want to use <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Logic/Equiv/Basic.html#Equiv.subtypeQuotientEquivQuotientSubtype\">Equiv.subtypeQuotientEquivQuotientSubtype</a> to reduce your problem to lifting a non-dependent function?</p>",
        "id": 518360260,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1747329514
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Try using <code>Quotient.rec</code>?</p>",
